Greek Debt Rescheduling Cost Put at 20 Billion Euros, FT Says

-- B y   A l a n   P u r k i s s
-- 
2011-06-15T07:40:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-15/greek-debt-rescheduling-cost-put-at-20-billion-euros-ft-says.html
A Greek debt rescheduling plan
inspired by  Germany  might force eurozone governments to provide
as much as 20 billion euros ($29 billion) more, the Financial
Times reported, citing a briefing paper that was circulated to
finance ministers by the European Commission and that the
newspaper has reviewed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alan Purkiss in  London  on   apurkiss@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 